{
  "texts": [
    "Compared to the previous LLM-based AVSR model (Cappellazzo et al., 2024) that uses 25 tokens per second, our method reduces token usage by 86%.",
    "Additionally, our approach improves computational efficiency, reducing FLOPs by 35.7%.",
    "Audio-based automatic speech recognition is a well-studied and one of the most frequently used technology (Amodei et al., 2016; Kim et al., 2017; Prabhavalkar et al., 2023).",
    "However, as it primarily depends on acoustic inputs, its performance naturally degraded when the input audio is perturbed with other background noises (e.g., babble noise) (Varga and Steeneken, 1993).",
    "Visual Speech Recognition (VSR) aims to employ visual inputs only in speech recognition, using the fact that the visual inputs are not affected by the acoustic noises."
  ]
}